history.content:
From the 168 Piazza:

"I don't control the wait list.  Talk to Michael-David Sassoon in the CS department.  However, I can tell you that we are not expanding the class because we were not given enough funding to hire more TAs.  This is an outcome I fought hard to overturn, but I failed."

While we hope to accommodate all interested students, that may not be possible.  With 450 students enrolled and a waitlist of 90, my assumption is that all CS/EECS seniors who used their phase 1 to indicate taking this course was a priority for them are now, in fact, enrolled.

Other students will be enrolled into the class to take the place of currently enrolled students who drop to make other plans.  You maximize your chance to be enrolled by making sure the discussion section you have chosen still has some capacity.  At #16 on the waitlist, you have a fairly good chance but of course you need to have a backup plan now in case it doesn't work out.
